Library modules used by the Weather Station project.

This directory contains small, focused driver libraries and service stubs used by
the main application.

Layout
------

- `drivers/` — hardware drivers split by type (sensors, actuators).
	- `sensors/dht22/` — DHT22 sensor driver and configuration.
	- `actuators/buzzer/` — simple buzzer driver.
- `services/` — placeholders for network and cloud-related services (HTTP, MQTT, WiFi).

Usage
-----

Include headers from `lib` in your `src` files. Example (already used in `src/main.cpp`):

```cpp
#include <sensors/dht22/dht22_sensor.h>
#include <actuators/buzzer/buzzer_driver.h>

DHT22Sensor dht22;
void setup() {
	dht22.DHT22Init();
}
```

Extending
--------

Add new drivers or services by creating a subfolder and following the existing
header/implementation pattern. Keep APIs small and explicit so they are easy to
unit-test and mock.

Contributing
------------

- Add issues for new sensors or service integrations.
- Prefer descriptive commit messages and small PRs focused on a single device or service.

